Let x be the amount of fence {name1} gets and y be the amount {name2} gets. We know that y = x + {diff}, and y + x = {total}.
Substituting the first equation into the second equation, we get 2x+{diff}={total}
Subtracting the {diff} from both sides, we get 2x={total-diff}
We divide each side by two, leaving x={(total-diff)//2}. This means {name1} has {(total-diff)//2} {unit} of fence left over.
#### {(total-diff)//2}
